parameters: This is that forest... that rainy day, isn't it...
The day I ran away, and hurt Umi...
The day I couldn't trust Umi.
Meeting Umi, falling in love, being welcomed by everyone in the village...
That's right... at this moment... I couldn't take Umi's hand...
Because I didn't have the courage...
I didn't have the strength to face Umi...
I was afraid of getting hurt myself...
But... the one who suffered the most at this time must have been Umi...
Kru "I'm sorry... Umi... it must have been hard alone? Lonely, right..."
Umi "K...ru... I'm sorry... I'm so sorry..."
Kru "I'm sorry for making you fight alone... I'm sorry I didn't realize..."
Kru "I'm okay... because I made a promise..."
Kru "To always love Umi... forever and ever..."
Kru "Umi... no matter what happens, no matter how much you change..."
Kru "It's okay... We're going to be okay..."
There are so many things I want to redo...
We have to start from here...

The person I fell in love with... the person I hurt... I want to start over
with her...
I want to start over with that person once again...
Kru "Umi... I'm sorry it took so long..."
Kru "I'm sorry for leaving you all alone..."
Kru "You don't have to be scared anymore..."
Kru "I'll take away all of Umi's fears..."
Kru "So relax... and let yourself be held by me..."

Umi continued to cry without looking away as the morning sun shone down on
her...
The tears on her cheeks dissolved into the raindrops,
her cries dissolved into the rustling of the trees,
her body heat dissolved into the sunlight,
and our sins dissolved into the wind and disappeared somewhere...

What remained here was only our feelings for each other... Only love
remained, supporting our entire being.
The things I want to redo... such things...
There are so many of them...
If I were to count them, there would be no end...

Things from my childhood... since joining the army... about the people I
couldn't save...
And then... after meeting Umi... being taken away by Shif...

Damn it! I want to redo all of it! I want to believe it'll go well this
time!
But... Mia said... even if you repeat it many times...

It's probably just after having repeated it... and I've walked down the
wrong path over and over again...

Repeating it over and over... each time having Umi taken away... and
hurting Umi...
Thinking only I was suffering... thinking only I was betrayed...

That rainy day... the day everything came to light... the day I shook off
Umi's hand...

If only on that day... I had taken Umi's hand... if only I had believed in
her...
This is that forest... from that rainy day, isn't it?
That's right... at this moment... I couldn't take Umi's hand...

Kru: "I'm sorry... Umi... you must have been in pain alone? You must have
been lonely..."
Umi: "Kru... I'm sorry... I'm so sorry..."

Kru: "I'm sorry for making you fight alone... I'm sorry for not
realizing..."
Kru: "I'm okay... because I made a promise..."
Kru: "To always love Umi... forever and ever..."
Kru: "No matter what happens to Umi, no matter how much you change..."
Kru: "It's okay... we're going to be okay..."
The things I want to redo... such things...
There are so many of them...
I have to start from here...
I chose this... I hurt the person I love...
I want to start over again with that person...
Kru: "Umi... I'm sorry... it took so long..."
Kru: "I'm sorry... for leaving you all alone..."
Kru: "You don't have to be scared anymore..."
Kru: "I'll remove all of Umi's fears..."
Kru: "So relax... and let yourself be held by me..."
Umi continued to cry without looking away as the morning sun shone down...
The tears streaming down her cheeks dissolved into the raindrops,
her cries dissolved into the rustling of the trees,
her body heat dissolved into the sunlight,
and our sins dissolved into the wind and disappeared somewhere...

What remained here was only our feelings for each other... only love
remained, supporting our entire being.

Remembering that the soldiers would come to capture me, we moved to a
different location...
